title: Understand Data Types
text: In computer science, different kinds of data are categorized into types. For example, text is usually a 'string', numbers are 'int' or 'float', etc.

title: All Data Can Have Types
text: Every piece of data, whether it is a number, text, or complex object, has a specific data type that defines its nature and what kind of operations can be performed on it.

title: Does Text Have a Type?
text: Consider whether bits of text have associated types when programming?

title: Do Numbers Have a Type?
text: Think about numbers you use in coding. Are they associated with specific types?
